<div class="yui-content">
<div id="wiki-tab-0-0">
<p>/&gt; Welcome to the SCP Foundation personnel database. Please enter access credentials.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[PLEASE&nbsp;INPUT&nbsp;CREDENTIALS]</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Username:&nbsp;*******&nbsp;Password:&nbsp;*********</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Identity confirmed. Welcome,</p>


<p><strong>[ACCESSING FILE&#8230;COMPLETE]</strong></p>
<p><strong>Name:</strong> Lucius Elijah Veritas</p>
<p><strong>Security Clearance:</strong> 4</p>
<p><strong>Current Assignment:</strong> Director of Research (SCP-914).</p>
<p><strong>Position:</strong> Head of Experimental Security.</p>
<p><strong>Former Position:</strong> Humanoid Psychology.</p>
<p><strong>Current Location:</strong> Site-19-23.</p>
<p><strong>Serial Number:</strong> 3475-83537</p>
<p><strong>Profile:</strong> Specialised in personnel/humanoid interaction and Experimental Security, Veritas' primary position is the Director of Research overseeing and mandating testing on <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-914">SCP-914</a>.</p>
<p>While he started working with humanoid objects, the overseeing of tests involving SCP-914 has been his full-time job for several years. During these years, his management has been described from ''strict, but fair'' to ''despotic and dictatorial''.</p>
<p>While generally unsociable, it is no secret that he is close friends with <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/new-technical-issues">Technical Researcher Rosen</a> and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/dr-rogets-file">Dr. Roget</a>.</p>
<p>Since testing with SCP-914 is considered to be a ''test of professional skill'' by a portion of new researchers, Dr. Veritas currently holds the record of ''termination of most personnel outside of O5 command'', with 132.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>FROM:</strong> Dr. Daniels, Junior Researcher, Site 19<br />
<strong>TO:</strong> Dr. Gears, [REDACTED]<br />
<strong>SUBJECT:</strong> Testing with 914</p>
<p>Gears, can you get Veritas off my back? I promise to be careful this time, I even read and signed his stupid <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-914-experiment-log-guidelines">security manual for 914</a> three times!</p>
<p>~ Junior Researcher Daniels.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>FROM:</strong> Dr. Gears, [REDACTED]<br />
<strong>TO:</strong> Dr. Daniels, Junior Researcher, Site 19<br />
<strong>SUBJECT:</strong> RE: Testing with 914</p>
<p>Dear Dr. Daniels,</p>
<p>According to the testing logs from two weeks ago, you attempted to 'refine' a flamethrower, which resulted in considerable damage to SCP-914's containment chamber and SCP-914 itself. The repairs are still being made at the time of writing. I was not present at the time of testing, but at least two researchers described the result as, and I quote: ''Something you would see in a Terminator movie''. While I am not familiar with the particular film, Dr. Julie is still in therapy following the incident. I feel forced to side with Dr. Veritas on this one.</p>
<p>~ Dr. Gears.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
</div>
